Annotation Types Summary
FailingTest If this interface is contained anywhere inside of a CompilationUnit, that compilation unit will be analyzed as a test, and the analysis of that file should produce errors or warnings.
MultiAnnotation  
PassingTest If this interface is contained anywhere inside of a CompilationUnit, that compilation unit will be analyzed as a test, and the analysis of that file should produce no errors or warnings.
UseAnalyses An annotation that indicates which analyses should be used to test this file.
 

Package edu.cmu.cs.crystal.annotations Description

This package contains annotations used by the Crystal Static Analysis Framework that facilitate writing and testing Java analyses written based on Crystal.

  • MultiAnnotation allows living more easily with Java's restriction of one annotation of a given type per annotated element.
  • PassingTest, FailingTest, and UseAnalyses facilitate regression-testing analyses using Crystal's AnnotatedTest JUnit test driver.
